sql:
SELECT SUM(current_amount) AS total_earnings, COUNT(*) AS number_of_earnings
FROM employee_earnings
WHERE employee_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
External knowledge:
- "Top-level employees" refers to employees with no manager (manager_id IS NULL), indicating they are at the highest level of the organizational hierarchy;
- Hierarchical level represents the position of an employee within the organizational structure, with level 1 being the top;
- "Subordinates" refers to employees who report directly or indirectly to another employee in the hierarchy.

sql:
SELECT SUM(amount) AS total_mandatory_deductions
FROM employee_deductions
WHERE is_mandatory = 1;

SELECT MAX(
    (SELECT SUM(current_amount) FROM employee_earnings ee WHERE ee.employee_id = e.employee_id) - 
    (SELECT SUM(amount) FROM employee_deductions ed WHERE ed.employee_id = e.employee_id)
) AS highest_net_earnings
FROM employees e;

external_knowledge:
- Top department refers to the highest level in the department hierarchy; 
- Average gross salary and average net salary are calculated over all payroll periods for each employee; 
- Mandatory benefits and deductions are those where the is_mandatory flag is 1; 
- Taxable earnings refer to the portion of earnings that are subject to tax.

sql:
SELECT earning_id, SUM(arrears + current_amount) AS total_earnings
FROM employee_earnings
GROUP BY earning_id;
